# Electron UI Rules

- Keep renderer code inside `ElectronApp/src/renderer/src/` with feature-first structure: layout/router modules, `pages/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `services/`.
- Keep frontend as console-only: no runtime authority logic in React components, hooks, or local stores.
- Route runtime operations through typed service abstractions (`services/daemonApi.ts`) and IPC bridge; do not call core internals directly.
- Keep interactions asynchronous and resilient; surface daemon errors with clear user feedback.
- Keep platform-only capabilities behind preload IPC APIs; do not enable unsafe Node integration in renderer.
- Keep page logic split by concern; avoid dumping multiple pages or feature flows into one file.
- Persist only UI preferences in frontend; runtime config/state belongs to core daemon.

## Example

```ts
// BAD: parse subscription payload and mutate runtime state in React component
// GOOD: call daemon API -> core handles parsing/persistence -> component renders returned snapshot
```
